metadata.name: Windows Of Opportunity #214
metadata.description: Windows Of Opportunity displays generative stained glass like artworks in which numerous variables ensure that each mint is unique. Rare features have been implemented. 1 year of blood sweat and tears have been injected in each output. Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Rainbow Maffs! #72
metadata.description: Living rainbows created with the power of maths! Yes Maths, that subject we all zoned out during. Who'd have thought that sine and cosine would actually be useful.

metadata.name: Theatergoers #124
metadata.description:
Simple black and white blobs align to create delicate stories of an audience at their local theater. Follow their eyes in each piece to get started, but don't stare for too long——that's rude.

- press 's' to save the image at its current resolution
- press 'h' to say hello

20% of primary sales will be donated to https://www.cityarts.org/ and minters will receive a small royalty for all secondary sales. 

Made with <3 and p5js | License: CC BY-NC-ND

metadata.name: Generational Differences #153
metadata.description:
Based on 1-dimensional cellular automata, different pleasing patterns are produced by each generation changing the rules for the next one. Each token will produce a unique sequence of patterns, like a slideshow of mosaics. Transitions may be subtle or very drastical, since a small change on the rules has a huge effect.
Best enjoyed on fullscreen

Click anywhere on the canvas to stop/resume the creation of new generations.
Press s to download at the current resolution

Original minters will get 50% of the royalties

How diverse can nature be?
